&lt;/div&gt; 
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Event_store&quot;&gt;Event store&lt;/a&gt; is a proper name for a..., well, storage of events. Events are &lt;strong&gt;facts&lt;/strong&gt; from the &lt;strong&gt;past&lt;/strong&gt;. Such a trait makes our storage a great candidate for &lt;span style=&quot;color: #ff0201;&quot;&gt;&lt;code&gt;append-only&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/span&gt; mode, ie. there are only two operations available: &lt;span style=&quot;color: #ff0201;&quot;&gt;&lt;code&gt;read&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/span&gt; and &lt;span style=&quot;color: #ff0201;&quot;&gt;&lt;code&gt;add&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/span&gt;. It might feel like a weird constraint but it allows to optimize mentioned operations to be as fast as possible. At the same time, simplicity creates a foundation for our creativity and making really complicated solutions.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
